                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4277a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-04">May 4,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>187. Reports from Rome are conflicting in detail as to exact progress of Italian
                    troops and contain no precise information as to entrance into Addis Ababa, but
                    it is generally said Badoglio will arrive there tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
